				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="2">The Scars of Velious ships to stores!</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</b></a>
				[12/4/2000-6:23:17 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=291813"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[1]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
ALL ABOARD!
EVERQUEST(r): THE SCARS OF VELIOUS(tm) SHIPS TO STORES<P>

-- Ancient Enemies, Frozen Wastes, and New Adventures Await "EverQuest" Faithful 
in Expansion Pack to Most Successful Online Role Playing Game --<P>

SAN DIEGO, Calif. - December 4, 2000 - Sony Online Entertainment announced today 
that EverQuest(r): The Scars of Velious(tm) will be available at retail stores 
tomorrow.  Velious provides the 300,000 plus current EverQuest gamers with an 
all-new frozen continent, 19 all-new adventure zones, numerous new creatures, 
additional spells and weapons and enhanced 3D game graphics engine.<P>

EverQuest: The Scars of Velious takes players on a mystical quest to the ice 
continent of Velious.  Once there, players will face all-new challenges and rewards 
in their quest for dominance and survival.  The new frozen continent, Velious, 
is located south of Antonica, and its 19 new zones include ice caves, crystal 
caverns, crypts, dungeons and frozen towers. The expansion pack features visually 
stunning non-player characters including frost giants, ice dragons, snow orcs, 
cave bears, Snowfang gnolls, storm giants and vicious ottermen. The highly-detailed 
world features three times the amount of polygons and larger textures than the 
current EverQuest world. <P>

"We are thrilled to announce that Velious is open and ready for exploration," 
said Scott McDaniel, executive director of marketing, Sony Online Entertainment. 
"The EverQuest fans will embark on a series of new adventures and come face-to-face 
with new creatures and don new graphically enhanced player armor."<P>

EverQuest: The Scars of Velious is the first expansion pack that requires a separate 
purchase of "EverQuest." Players will need to purchase a prior version of the 
game in order to experience Velious, and it is recommended that they have advanced 
characters in the level 35 or higher range to board ships to the new continent.<P>

During peak periods, EverQuest adventurers and dragon slayers can form alliances 
with up to 70,000 other players simultaneously.  The active global EverQuest 
subscriber base is comprised of players from various countries throughout the 
''real'' world, including the U.S., England, Canada, Singapore, Zimbabwe, Saudi 
Arabia, France and New Zealand.<P>

The Scars of Velious box cover features newly created art by famous fantasy artist 
Keith Parkinson and will have an SRP of $19.95.<P>

The official provider of EverQuest is <a href="http://www.station.com">www.station.com</a>, with software updates 
and news about the game, message boards and other community features, as well 
as an easy-to-use billing system for the EverQuest monthly subscription fee of 
$9.89.   For more information about EverQuest: The Scars of Velious please visit 
<a href="http://www.station.com/everquest/">www.station.com/everquest/</a>.
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="3">Brad McQuaid on Scars shipping</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
