				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037021.html">Scars of Velious in stores Tomorrow</a></B><P>

Just letting everyone know that Scars of Velious should start to appear in US stores tomorrow, and be in most stores by the end of the week.<P>

I'm not sure about outside of the US, but we do have much better distribution now. I'll try to find out.<P>

-Brad<P>

ps. If you have any Velious sightings, feel free to post them on this thread :)<P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

For those in San Diego, remember the team will be at the EB in UTC on Wednesday to say hi, sign boxes, give away posters, etc. <P>

See you there :)<P>

And stevemorley, yep, I've been shown quite a tour through the varous zones in Velious, and it's pretty darn amazing stuff :) I think the teams have really outdone themselves this time.<P>

For example, I'm really happy to see traps! (Especially after having so many Rogues upset with me for so long :)<P> 

Also, wow, are there some great stories and quests! We've seen a lot of posts asking for more stories, more RP, and more depth... well, Velious is a HUGE step forward in that direction -- there are all sorts of new scripted events involving players and NPCs using some advanced AI enchancements we managed to get implemented.<P>

I can't wait to hear what you all think :)<P>

-Brad
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
