				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="15">Scheduled Downtime Reminder</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</b></a>
				[12/3/2000-10:55:17 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=290802"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[19]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
The servers are set to come offline at 6:00am Pacific Standard Time (GMT-8) for an estimated period of 6 hours. This downtime is to prepare the servers for the Scars of Velious EverQuest expansion, but there's no word yet if the game will be for sale in stores by tomorrow. For clarification, Verant has stated (barring early sales) that as soon as you can buy Velious in the stores you will be able to play online, so we can only hope everything is ready to go by tomorrow. <P>

 Anyway, if you would like to join your fellow EQ players on our <a href="http://www.everlore.com/chat/default.asp">IRC Chat Room</a> and chat to help pass the downtime you're more than welcome to stop by. We'll be offering trivia, network status updates, and lively conversation to help pass the time tomorrow, so it's highly recommended you drop by and see what's going on.<P>

Also we're still running our item price contest, so make sure you submit as many accurate item prices as possible to our <a href="http://www.everlore.com/items/">Equipment Database</a>, the most submissions win's the prize! Also three runners up will be selected at random for all price submissions received for that week, so you've got quite a few chances to win! Enjoy!<P>

Catalyst<BR>
Everlore News Editor
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
