				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
December 3rd, 7:00pm<BR>
------------------------------<P>

<B>*Velious Preparation*</B><P>

The files just pushed to your client are in preparation for the launch of EverQuest: The Scars of Velious.  Please read EQManual_Supplement.doc (or .txt) in your EverQuest directory for information on new features, some of them Velious-specific, which will be included in tomorrow's patch.<P>

- The EverQuest Team
</blockquote>
Also, if you're having trouble grabbing this patch from the server, this message was recently entered to explain a bit about what's going on.
<Blockquote>
<B>Patcher Connectivity Issues</B> Sun Dec 3 18:58:32 PST 2000<P>

In preparation for the Velious release, we have patched a portion of tomorrow's data tonight to ease the amount of time required for the full patch. Due to heavy loads on our patchers, your download times may vary. <P>

- The EverQuest Team 
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="17">Alan VanCouvering on the EQ naming policy</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</b></a>
				[12/3/2000-5:37:46 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=290565"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[65]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036440.html">Name Nazi's Out of Control on VZ</a></B><P>

Well it worked. The name police turned out in force. So now, that I know of, 2 level 60's on our server have decided to quit playing because their name got changed. They've had the names for over a year, they were not offensive in any way, but the name nazis decided it's never too late to annoy the customers.<P>

For example, one of the players was named "Preecha". That's been his identity. Here's someone who's a well known high level, who's helped kill Trakanon several times, and now his name has been changed for no good reason. (Those who know me from VZ know I'm no fan of Preecha or his guild, but seeing someone quit the game because CUSTOMER SERVICE (lol) decided it was time to screw them over for something as stupid as a name is just ludicrous.<P>

<B>If you want to discuss our name policies, I'm all for it. But not with the kind of language and name calling that has been used in this thread.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036481.html">Name "dictators" out of control on VZ</a></B><P>

Look at the picture here. The people invested over 100 days into their virtual selves, and about 30 days into it some policy was made up, by which ONE person MIGHT find the name in violation of that said policy. So, 70 days later, sure enough, it gets changed.
First Anyone, then Oreh Ta'Egral, now Preecha Grogsmash Dahummies, Graym, Karn etc etc. This people are royally ripped that after 100 days, some jerk decided to take a cheap shot at them by petitioning them. <P>

<B>I'm sorry that the name changes bother you so much. But it's not as though we've hidden the rules about naming characters. It is unfortunate that names breaking the rules remain in the game so long, and therefore the players get attached to them. But the rules are pretty clear, and we do our best to stick by our rules as tightly as we can. And those rules have existed since the game was opened, not thirty days into it.<P>

Again, I'm sorry if the name changes upset anyone, but we're pretty firm about it and we think that it adds a lot to the game to have charactes with names that fit the setting.<P>

Alan</B>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="18">Paladins of Norrath has a new host</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</b></a>
				[12/3/2000-5:37:23 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=290554"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[1]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
Casters Realm is now hosting the Paladins of Norrath website.

<p>After a long time at the helm Varrus Aurelius has finally retired from the world of Norrath and rather than see perhaps the most valuable Paladin site online fall into decline, we at Casters Realm have picked up where he has left off.
<p>You can access the Paladins of Norrath website at <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/pon">http://eq.castersrealm.com/pon</a>.</p>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="19">Brell Serilis: GM Event in Butcherblock Mountains</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:">Rashandar Soulstalker</b></a>
				[12/3/2000-10:27:57 AM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=289811"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[4]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
On Saturday there was a GM event held in the Butcherblock Mountains on Brell, around 6:30pm MST. The event consisted of 3 named dragons: Blade Wing, Dark Wing, and Death Wing. The dragons were estimated to be mid teens in level. Anyone over level 30 was unable to attack them. I sat nearby and watched the newbies hack away, healing, buffing, and DSing as I saw fit :)<P>


Rashandar Soulstalker<BR>
35th Druid of Brell<BR>
Officer of Divine Aura<P>

<a href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenShot.asp?ID=289816">Image #1</a><BR>
<a href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenShot.asp?ID=289818">Image #2</a>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="20">Luclin: Steamfont gnomies GM event</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:">Gerald Tarrant</b></a>
				[12/3/2000-10:27:24 AM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=290256"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[4]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
Last night around 11 PM EST in Steamfont there appeared a hunting party of ogres near the Steamfont mines, around lvl 10. For various reasons a level 44 was not able to attack the ogres, and the ogres would only attack small races, there were three gnome and one dwarf casualties. As the ogres near'd Ak'anon, they came under the attack of gnome GM's also lvl 10, and a small party of adventurers, led by Wildlife Avenger, ranger of Luclin. The battle raged for a little while in front of the guards, finally ending with the bodies of ogres on the ground. The ogres had a Damask Robe on one along with bone chips, which was given to Eliniar, and a Silver Jaded Ring. At the end of the battle awards were given to the adventurers by the gnomes, among the rewards were banded and bronze armor, in limited amounts. All in all it was a success, at the least an informative lesson on how to make Gnome Sandwhiches (magic no rent). Thanks GMs and Guides of Luclin!<P>

